This paper presents a study using deep fully convolutional network and ensemble models to automatically detect white matter hyperintensities (WMH) using magnetic resonance (MR) scans. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) are also possible sub-categories, as the paper uses deep learning techniques and analyzes MR images.
